From: nix-on-z <nix-on-z@users.noreply.github.com>
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] openssl: add s390x-linux cross-compilation target

When cross-compiling OpenSSL for s390x, the configure script selection
falls through to "linux-generic64", which misses s390x-specific
optimizations:

  - CPACF hardware crypto acceleration (AES, SHA, GHASH in hardware)
  - s390x assembly-optimized routines
  - Proper 64-bit s390x ABI handling

OpenSSL has a dedicated "linux64-s390x" target that enables all of
these. Add it to the platform-specific configureScript map, matching
the pattern used for other architectures (ARM, x86_64, PPC, RISC-V).

This is significant for performance: CPACF provides near-zero-cost
AES-256 and SHA-256, which Nix uses extensively for store path hashing.

diff --git a/pkgs/development/libraries/openssl/default.nix b/pkgs/development/libraries/openssl/default.nix
index XXXXXXX..XXXXXXX 100644
--- a/pkgs/development/libraries/openssl/default.nix
+++ b/pkgs/development/libraries/openssl/default.nix
@@ -149,6 +149,7 @@
           riscv64-linux = "./Configure linux64-riscv64";
+          s390x-linux = "./Configure linux64-s390x";
         }
